Reasoning: The paper discusses the creation of a parallel bilingual corpora of web publications using automated translation and empiric-statistic rules. This involves natural language processing (NLP) techniques such as morphological analysis and dictionaries, which are commonly used in the fields of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of automated translation also suggests a connection to artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG, cs.DL).
